article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 56, Texas-Pan American 54
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Dominique Whatley hit a 35-foot 3-pointer as time expired, lifting Bethune-Cookman to a 56-54 victory Saturday over Texas-Pan American in the Las Vegas Holiday Classic. Josh Cummings made it 54-53 with 23.6 seconds left, and after Texas-Pan American's Danny Puente missed a foul shot, the Wildcats grabbed the rebound. A loose ball near midcourt ended up with Whatley, who hit the long game-winner. Whatley finished with 18 points and John Holmes had 12 for the Wildcats (5-6), who overcame a 15-point second-half deficit with a 23-9 run over the final 6:43. Bethune-Cookman shot 70 percent from the field in the second half. Texas-Pan American (6-8) got a game-high 19 points and 10 rebounds from Nathan Hawkins, while Brian Burrell and Zach Trader added 10 points each.
